<subSubSection box="[189,508,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,1193]" box="[189,508,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,508,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="Salm-Dyck" authorityName="Salm-Dyck" authorityYear="1840" box="[262,503,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cereeae">Cereeae Salm-Dyck</taxonomicName>
:
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,158,1193]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">
— 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[536,812,158,184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli (2010)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a broader circumscription of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salm-Dyck" authorityYear="1840" box="[1361,1451,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cereeae">Cereeae</taxonomicName>
than traditional concepts (see e.g., Anderson 2001, 2005, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hunt, D. &amp; Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G." box="[807,1004,194,221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" refId="ref17187" refString="Hunt, D., Taylor, N. &amp; Charles, G. (2013) The New Cactus Lexicon, Atlas of Illustrations. Dh Books, Milborn Port, 373 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Hunt 
<emphasis box="[873,933,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lendel, A." box="[1026,1189,194,221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="11 - 12" refId="ref17791" refString="Lendel, A. (2006) Phylogenetic relationships in the tribe Trichocereeae (Cacteae) inferred from cpDNA sequence data analysis. IOS Bulletin 14: 11 - 12" type="journal article" year="2006">Lendel (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritz, C. &amp; Martins, L. &amp; Mecklenburg, R. &amp; Goremykin, V. &amp; Hellwig, F. H." box="[1250,1451,194,220]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="1321 - 1332" refId="ref18437" refString="Ritz, C., Martins, L., Mecklenburg, R., Goremykin, V. &amp; Hellwig, F. H. (2007) The molecular phylogeny of Rebutia (Cactaceae) and its allies demonstrates the influence of paleography on the evolution of South American mountain cacti. American Journal of Botany 94: 1321 - 1332. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 94.8.1321" type="journal article" year="2007">
Ritz 
<emphasis box="[1307,1367,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="95">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
showed, in fact, that the traditionally circumscribed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salm-Dyck" authorityYear="1840" box="[749,839,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cereeae">Cereeae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[901,1059,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Trichocereeae">Trichocereeae</taxonomicName>
are not monophyletic. Therefore, we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U." box="[260,558,266,292]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref18353" refString="Nyffeler, R. &amp; Eggli, U. (2010) A farewell to dated ideas and concepts: molecular phylogenetics and a revised suprageneric classification of the family Cactaceae. Schumannia 6: 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2010">Nyffeler &amp; Eggli’s (2010)</bibRefCitation>
concept of a tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salm-Dyck" authorityYear="1840" box="[777,867,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Cereeae">Cereeae</taxonomicName>
with three subtribes, i.e. Cereinae Britton &amp; Rose, 
<taxonomicName authority="Donald" authorityName="Donald" box="[136,346,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Rebutiinae">Rebutiinae Donald</taxonomicName>
(incl. Browningieae Buxb.) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" box="[714,1063,302,329]" pageId="16" pageNumber="95" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Trichocereinae">Trichocereinae Britton &amp; Rose</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
